Marriage they say is between a man and a woman and all third parties beware. This is not the case for the union between the Ooni of Ife, Oba Enitan Adeyeye Ogunwusi and prophetess Naomi Oluwaseyi. Since news broke that the traditional ruler had plans to marry a new wife, of course, everyone clamoured to know the identity of the lucky maiden. Alas, she is a prophetess and some people are expressing their unsought concern with the seeming conflicting interest in religion forgetting that love they say, conquers all. Read More: Update: Prophetess Naomi Oluwaseyi Is The New Queen Of Ife But that has not stopped some concerned individuals from expressing their thoughts in the matter via Twitter.        